{
  "texts": [
    "For intent classification, our findings consistently demonstrated that encoder-only models outperformed their decoder-only counterparts.",
    "This superiority was particularly pronounced in datasets with numerous classes, suggesting that the encoder's ability to capture holistic representations of input text contributed to better class differentiation.",
    "Interestingly, decoder-only models exhibited sensitivity to class names, potentially indicating challenges in extracting relevant information solely from the decoding process.",
    "Shifting the focus to sentiment analysis, fine-tuned decoder-only models showcased a slight advantage over encoder-only models.",
    "However, this advantage diminished when confronted with datasets featuring a higher number of sentiment classes, especially when extending beyond the binary positive and negative categories."
  ]
}